@startuml
title Resource Pooling Architecture - Pool Composition

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/package-diagram-style.iuml

package "Sample Resource Pool" as Pool {

  package "CPU Sub-pool" as CPUP {
    rectangle "CPU cores\n(allocated to virtual servers)" as CPUs
  }

  package "Memory Sub-pool" as MEMP {
    rectangle "Physical RAM\n(for new or scaled servers)" as RAM
  }

  package "Cloud Storage\nSub-pool" as STP {
    database "File-based or\nblock-based storage" as STO
  }

  package "Virtual Network\nSub-pool" as NETP {
    rectangle "Preconfigured\nnetwork devices" as NETD
  }
}

note right of Pool
  Dedicated pools per IT resource type
  can be grouped into a larger pool;
  each individual pool then becomes a
  sub-pool.
end note

package "Other Pool Types Mentioned" as Others {
  rectangle "Physical Server Pool" as PSP
  rectangle "Virtual Server Pool" as VSP
  rectangle "Network Pool\n(interconnect pool)" as NP
}

note bottom of Others
  Virtual server pools are configured
  from templates chosen at provisioning
  (e.g., Windows 4 GB, Ubuntu 2 GB).
end note

@enduml

